{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I just want to tell you my story."},{"time":2000,"text":"I spend a lot of time"},{"time":4000,"text":"teaching adults how to use visual language"},{"time":6000,"text":"and doodling in the workplace."},{"time":8000,"text":"And naturally, I encounter a lot of resistance,"},{"time":11000,"text":"because it's considered to be anti-intellectual"},{"time":14000,"text":"and counter to serious learning."},{"time":16000,"text":"But I have a problem with that belief,"},{"time":18000,"text":"because I know that doodling has a profound impact"},{"time":21000,"text":"on the way that we can process information"},{"time":24000,"text":"and the way that we can solve problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"So I was curious about why there was a disconnect"},{"time":29000,"text":"between the way our society perceives doodling"},{"time":31000,"text":"and the way that the reality is."},{"time":33000,"text":"So I discovered some very interesting things."},{"time":36000,"text":"For example, there's no such thing"},{"time":38000,"text":"as a flattering definition of a doodle."},{"time":41000,"text":"In the 17th century, a doodle was a simpleton or a fool --"},{"time":44000,"text":"as in Yankee Doodle."},{"time":46000,"text":"In the 18th century, it became a verb,"},{"time":48000,"text":"and it meant to swindle or ridicule or to make fun of someone."},{"time":51000,"text":"In the 19th century, it was a corrupt politician."},{"time":54000,"text":"And today, we have what is perhaps our most offensive definition,"},{"time":57000,"text":"at least to me, which is the following:"},{"time":59000,"text":"To doodle officially means"},{"time":61000,"text":"to dawdle,"},{"time":63000,"text":"to dilly dally, to monkey around,"},{"time":65000,"text":"to make meaningless marks,"},{"time":67000,"text":"to do something of little value, substance or import,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and -- my personal favorite --"},{"time":72000,"text":"to do nothing."},{"time":74000,"text":"No wonder people are averse to doodling at work."},{"time":77000,"text":"Doing nothing at work is akin to masturbating at work;"},{"time":79000,"text":"it's totally inappropriate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"Additionally, I've heard horror stories"},{"time":85000,"text":"from people whose teachers scolded them, of course, for doodling in classrooms."},{"time":88000,"text":"And they have bosses who scold them for doodling in the boardroom."},{"time":91000,"text":"There is a powerful cultural norm against doodling"},{"time":94000,"text":"in settings in which we are supposed to learn something."},{"time":97000,"text":"And unfortunately,"},{"time":99000,"text":"the press tends to reinforce this norm"},{"time":101000,"text":"when they're reporting on a doodling scene --"},{"time":103000,"text":"of an important person at a confirmation hearing and the like --"},{"time":106000,"text":"they typically use words like \"discovered\""},{"time":108000,"text":"or \"caught\" or \"found out,\""},{"time":110000,"text":"as if there's some sort of criminal act being committed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113000,"text":"And additionally, there is a psychological aversion to doodling --"},{"time":116000,"text":"thank you, Freud."},{"time":118000,"text":"In the 1930s, Freud told us all"},{"time":120000,"text":"that you could analyze people's psyches"},{"time":122000,"text":"based on their doodles."},{"time":124000,"text":"This is not accurate, but it did happen to Tony Blair"},{"time":126000,"text":"at the Davos Forum in 2005,"},{"time":128000,"text":"when his doodles were, of course, \"discovered\""},{"time":131000,"text":"and he was labeled the following things."},{"time":134000,"text":"Now it turned out to be Bill Gates' doodle."},{"time":138000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":140000,"text":"And Bill, if you're here, nobody thinks you're megalomaniacal."},{"time":144000,"text":"But that does contribute"},{"time":146000,"text":"to people not wanting to share their doodles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"And here is the real deal. Here's what I believe."},{"time":151000,"text":"I think that our culture"},{"time":153000,"text":"is so intensely focused on verbal information"},{"time":155000,"text":"that we're almost blinded to the value of doodling."},{"time":158000,"text":"And I'm not comfortable with that."},{"time":160000,"text":"And so because of that belief that I think needs to be burst,"},{"time":163000,"text":"I'm here to send us all hurtling back to the truth."},{"time":165000,"text":"And here's the truth:"},{"time":167000,"text":"doodling is an incredibly powerful tool,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and it is a tool that we need to remember and to re-learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"So here's a new definition for doodling."},{"time":175000,"text":"And I hope there's someone in here from The Oxford English Dictionary,"},{"time":177000,"text":"because I want to talk to you later."},{"time":179000,"text":"Here's the real definition:"},{"time":181000,"text":"Doodling is really to make spontaneous marks to help yourself think."},{"time":184000,"text":"That is why millions of people doodle."},{"time":187000,"text":"Here's another interesting truth about the doodle:"},{"time":189000,"text":"People who doodle when they're exposed to verbal information"},{"time":191000,"text":"retain more of that information"},{"time":193000,"text":"than their non-doodling counterparts."},{"time":196000,"text":"We think doodling is something you do when you lose focus,"},{"time":198000,"text":"but in reality, it is a preemptive measure"},{"time":200000,"text":"to stop you from losing focus."},{"time":203000,"text":"Additionally, it has a profound effect"},{"time":205000,"text":"on creative problem-solving"},{"time":207000,"text":"and deep information processing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"There are four ways that learners intake information"},{"time":211000,"text":"so that they can make decisions."},{"time":213000,"text":"They are visual, auditory,"},{"time":216000,"text":"reading and writing and kinesthetic."},{"time":219000,"text":"Now in order for us to really chew on information"},{"time":221000,"text":"and do something with it,"},{"time":223000,"text":"we have to engage at least two of those modalities,"},{"time":226000,"text":"or we have to engage one of those modalities"},{"time":228000,"text":"coupled with an emotional experience."},{"time":230000,"text":"The incredible contribution of the doodle"},{"time":233000,"text":"is that it engages all four learning modalities simultaneously"},{"time":236000,"text":"with the possibility of an emotional experience."},{"time":239000,"text":"That is a pretty solid contribution"},{"time":241000,"text":"for a behavior equated with doing nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"This is so nerdy,"},{"time":246000,"text":"but this made me cry when I discovered this."},{"time":248000,"text":"So they did anthropological research"},{"time":250000,"text":"into the unfolding of artistic activity in children,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and they found that, across space and time,"},{"time":255000,"text":"all children exhibit the same evolution in visual logic"},{"time":258000,"text":"as they grow."},{"time":260000,"text":"In other words, they have a shared and growing"},{"time":262000,"text":"complexity in visual language"},{"time":264000,"text":"that happens in a predictable order."},{"time":266000,"text":"And I think that is incredible."},{"time":268000,"text":"I think that means doodling is native to us"},{"time":270000,"text":"and we simply are denying ourselves that instinct."},{"time":274000,"text":"And finally, a lot a people aren't privy to this,"},{"time":276000,"text":"but the doodle is a precursor"},{"time":278000,"text":"to some of our greatest cultural assets."},{"time":280000,"text":"This is but one:"},{"time":282000,"text":"this is Frank Gehry the architect's precursor to the Guggenheim in Abu Dhabi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"So here is my point:"},{"time":287000,"text":"Under no circumstances should doodling be eradicated"},{"time":290000,"text":"from a classroom or a boardroom"},{"time":292000,"text":"or even the war room."},{"time":294000,"text":"On the contrary,"},{"time":296000,"text":"doodling should be leveraged in precisely those situations"},{"time":299000,"text":"where information density is very high"},{"time":301000,"text":"and the need for processing that information is very high."},{"time":304000,"text":"And I will go you one further."},{"time":306000,"text":"Because doodling is so universally accessible"},{"time":309000,"text":"and it is not intimidating as an art form,"},{"time":311000,"text":"it can be leveraged as a portal"},{"time":313000,"text":"through which we move people"},{"time":315000,"text":"into higher levels of visual literacy."},{"time":318000,"text":"My friends, the doodle has never been"},{"time":320000,"text":"the nemesis of intellectual thought."},{"time":322000,"text":"In reality, it is one of its greatest allies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":326000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}